result.execSummary:
The defendant Gabriel Thomas was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: AS TO ALL COUNTS: Consecutive. Straight time.

miscConds.notes:
CONDITIONS AS TO ALL COUNTS:
Batterers Intervention program. Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment. Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
No contact with victim, without approval of the court or agent. Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER.
Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Court WAIVED all non-mandatory costs, fees, and surcharges.

No contact with firearms. Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Gabriel Thomas in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Evan Glaberson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.

Defendant Gabriel Thomas in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  William T. Berens appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Court admonished defendant for non-compliance, court did not order condition time be served at this time. Case adjourned for additional review.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for December 19, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Gabriel Thomas NOT in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Evan Glaberson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DOC Agent NOT in court. Discussion regarding missed court date, agent to follow up with defendant. Report received & Filed. Court adjourned case for Probation Review Hearing in branch 23.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for September 19, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.
AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to 2 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive, with credit for 56 DAYS time served, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 2 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 2 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 3
The court sentenced the defendant to 2 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive,  straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 2 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 25 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review (AS TO EACH COUNT)
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim, without approval of the court or agent.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
-Court WAIVED all non-mandatory costs, fees, and surcharges.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief. 
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER
*Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.

*Court DENIED Expungement in this matter.

Filed: 
-Pretrial Sentence Credit
-Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief
-Memorandum of Conditions of Probation

AS TO COUNTS 1, 2 & 3 AS AMENDED.
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Defendant Gabriel Thomas in court with attorney Christian T Eichenlaub.  Defendant Gabriel Thomas in custody.  Matthew G Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Parties have reached a resolution. Original AMENDED Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty. Count 1 & Count 3 Amended to Disorderly Conduct, Domestic Abuse, contrary to Wis. Stat 947.01(1), 939.51(3)(b), 968.075(1)(a), a class B Misdemeanor. Count 2 Amended to Criminal Damage to Property, Domestic Abuse, contrary to Wis. Stat. 943.01(1), 939.51(3)(a), 968.075(1)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for August 15, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Christian T Eichenlaub in court, defendant Gabriel Thomas not in court, in custody.  Matthew G Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 1st call, parties ready to proceed. Case passed to address court calendar.

Received & Filed, Letter to the court, the same (original) previously received by the court on 4/03/2014, and then removed by stipulation of parties from the court file on 4/08/2014. Letter returned to file by the defense.

Attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub in court, defendant Gabriel Thomas not in court, in custody.  Matthew G. Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant NOT produced.  Final Pretrial held. Parties ready to proceed to trial. Discussion regarding Letter from defendant to the court. Parties stipulate to withdraw the letter from the court file, copy provided to the state, original returned to the defense. Case adjourned to branch 23 for Jury Trial at 8:30 am on 04/30/2014.
Received & Filed, Letter to the court.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.

Defendant Gabriel Thomas in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Defendant Gabriel Thomas in custody.  Matthew G. Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case set for Preliminary Hearing. Defense counsel objected to the use of Hearsay, due to date of incident. For reasons placed on the record, the court DENIED defense objection. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state: Milwaukee Police Officer Marcin Pagcz.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case set for Final Pretrial & Jury Trial in branch 23.

Attorney Michael Jude for Christian Thomas Eichenlaub in court, defendant Gabriel Thomas not in court, in custody.  Michael Schindhelm for Matthew G. Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant NOT produced from the House of Correction, unable to proceed with case. Case is adjourned to branch 23 for adjourned Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 20, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with MARCELLA S.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Gabriel Thomas in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Defendant Gabriel Thomas in custody.  Karine E. O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  Defendant pled not guilty TO MISDEMEANOR COUNTS 2 AND 3.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge GRADY, Branch 23.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 18, 2014 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
